"{\"uid\": \"deseret.com-utah-2024-05-22-scratch-and-sniff-stamp-ahead-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Getting mail from France?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 25, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 24, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999992349319853, \"rank\": 5.658356148101602e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Be sure to check out the stamp.\", \"from\": 26, \"to\": 57, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's La Poste has issued a uniquescratch-and-sniff stampas part of an effort to highlight the nation's heritage ahead of the2024 Summer Gamesin Paris.\", \"from\": 59, \"to\": 213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 59, \"end\": 65, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999992349319853, \"rank\": 5.658356148101602e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 68, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Poste_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9844971054506049, \"rank\": 0.01574700109051038, \"text\": \"La Poste\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Poste_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Poste_(France)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"La baguette de pain francaise\\\" is featured on the 1.96 euro ($2.12 in U.S. dollars) stamp for letters headed out of France, with a rendering of the ubiquitous long loaf of bread tied up in a blue, white and red tricolor striped ribbon representing the colors of the French flag.\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 286, \"end\": 298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.118649977107789e-23, \"text\": \"U.S. dollars\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\"}, {\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999992349319853, \"rank\": 5.658356148101602e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 482, \"end\": 493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yes, it's designed to emit \\\"bakery fragrances.\\\"\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anews releaseon the stamp, issued on May 16, the feast day of the patron saint of bakers, Saint Honor\\u00e9, raves about the French bread.\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 669, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baguette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bread\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baguette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baguette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The baguette, bread of our daily life, symbol of our gastronomy, jewel of our culture,\\\" it begins, describing the fresh-baked loaves that 12 million French customers buy daily from their local bakeries as \\\"the promise of a delectable sensory experience\\\" that \\\"seduces with its golden crust\\\" and \\\"transcends borders to become an international icon.\\\"\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 1033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8964711498390672, \"rank\": 0.11533750797042701, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not surprisingly, the stamp is attracting a lot more attention than the more traditional postage tied to the upcoming Olympics, featuring the bright redParis 2024 mascotsthat resemble revolutionary-era caps and well-known Parisian landmarks like the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stories about the stamps includes suggestions that the country's postal services stands to\\\"raise quite a bit of dough\\\"and an acknowledgment of the country's joie de vivre by saying, \\\"Leave it to the Frenchto find a way to pack the aroma of a freshly baked baguette into a postage stamp.\\\"\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joie_de_vivre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"joie de vivre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joie_de_vivre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joie_de_vivre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheBBC reportedthe fragrance comes from microcapsules in the Ink used on the stamps, quoting a printer who told French media that \\\"the difficulty for us is to apply this ink without breaking the capsules, so that the smell can then be released by the customer rubbing on the stamp.\\\"\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1701, \"end\": 1707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8964711498390672, \"rank\": 0.11533750797042701, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Salt Lake City hosted the2002 Winter Games, the U.S. Post Office issued stampsfeaturing winter sports.\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1878, \"end\": 1892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9990764722302343, \"rank\": 0.0009241252095161578, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no word yet on what type of stamps could be coming if the International Olympic Committee awards the2034 Winter Gamesto Utah in a vote scheduled to be held in Paris just before the start of the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2048, \"end\": 2079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2110, \"end\": 2114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999984443393991, \"rank\": 8.304357142595856e-07, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 2149, \"end\": 2154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.83898295261385e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe stamp designers could consider reviving one of the most popularOlympic pinsin 2002.\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Scratch-and-sniff green Jello stamps, anyone?\", \"from\": 2290, \"to\": 2335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2308, \"end\": 2319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Green_Jell\\u00ff\", \"score\": 0.9999975523931366, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"green Jello\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Green_Jell\\u00ff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Green_Jell\\u00ff\"}]}]}"